<p>Planigle is a Ruby on Rails based web application to help in planning Agile software development projects.  It uses Flex for its user interface. </p>

<p>To see a demo, go to <a href="http://www.planigle.com/demos">http://www.planigle.com/demos</a>.  To check out the most recent version, go to <a href="http://www.planigle.com/planigle/" rel="nofollow">www.planigle.com/planigle/</a> and sign up for your own account.  To view the backlog and give feedback on prioritization, go <a href="http://www.planigle.com/planigle/survey.html?projectid=1&surveykey=d51a97b5829c64aabd26e8577d6f5c114fceeb16" rel="nofollow">here</a>.  For any questions, issues or suggestions send email to <a href="mailto://support@planigle.com" rel="nofollow">Planigle Support</a>. </p>

<p>Planigle currently has the following features: </p>

<ul>
	<li>Backlog creation / prioritization </li>
	<li>Release tracking / planning </li>
	<li>Iteration planning / tracking </li>
</ul>
<img src="http://www.planigle.com/img/stories.png"> 

<ul>
	<li>Multi-tenancy (the ability to support multiple projects where project members can only see their own project) </li>
	<li>Support for multiple team projects </li>
</ul>
<img src="http://www.planigle.com/img/people.png">

<ul>
	<li>Task board </li>
</ul>
<img src="http://www.planigle.com/img/TaskBoard.png">